    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I am answering this because it's the top result in Google for \"String isBlank() Method\".</p>\n\n<p>If you are using Java 11 or above, you can use the <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/12/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/String.html#isBlank()\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">String class isBlank()</a> method. This method does the same thing as Apache Commons StringUtils class.</p>\n\n<p>I have written a small post on this method examples, read it <a href=\"https://www.javastring.net/java/string/java-string-isblank-method-examples\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">here</a>.</p>\n"
  }, {
