  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/23419087/stringutils-isblank-vs-string-isempty",
  "title" : "StringUtils.isBlank() vs String.isEmpty()",
  "body" : "<p>I ran into some code that has the following: </p>\n\n<pre><code>String foo = getvalue(\"foo\");\nif (StringUtils.isBlank(foo))\n    doStuff();\nelse\n    doOtherStuff();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This appears to be functionally equivalent to the following:</p>\n\n<pre><code>String foo = getvalue(\"foo\");\nif (foo.isEmpty())\n    doStuff();\nelse\n    doOtherStuff();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Is a difference between the two (<code>org.apache.commons.lang3.StringUtils.isBlank</code> and <code>java.lang.String.isEmpty</code>)?</p>\n"
